By default the consensus sequence is used as the reference sequence.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="boolean" name="bottom" qname="appInputs>bottom"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>If this is true then the reference sequence is displayed at the bottom of the alignment instead of the top.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="string" name="show" qname="appInputs>show" /><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="string" name="order" qname="appInputs>order" /><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="boolean" name="similarcase" qname="appInputs>similarcase"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>If this is set True, then when -show is set to 'Similarities' or 'Non-identities' and a residue is similar but not identical to the reference sequence residue, it will be changed to lower-case. If -show is set to 'All' then non-identical, non-similar residues will be changed to lower-case. They are separated by any non-digit, non-alpha character. Examples of region specifications are: 24-45, 56-78 1:45, 67=99;765..888 1,5,8,10,23,45,57,99</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="boolean" name="number" qname="appInputs>number"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>If this option is true then a line giving the positions in the alignment is displayed every 10 characters above the alignment.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="boolean" name="ruler" qname="appInputs>ruler"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>If this option is true then a ruler line marking every 5th and 10th character in the alignment is displayed.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="long" name="width" qname="appInputs>width" /><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="long" name="margin" qname="appInputs>margin"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>This sets the length of the left-hand margin for sequence names. If the margin is set at 0 then no margin and no names are displayed. If the margin is set to a value that is less than the length of a sequence name then the sequence name is displayed truncated to the length of the margin. If the margin is set to -1 then the minimum margin width that will allow all the sequence names to be displayed in full plus a space at the end of the name will automatically be selected.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="boolean" name="html" qname="appInputs>html" /><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="string" name="highlight" qname="appInputs>highlight"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>Regions to colour if formatting for HTML. If this is left blank, then the sequence is left alone. A set of regions is specified by a set of pairs of positions. The positions are integers. They are followed by any valid HTML font colour. Examples of region specifications are: 24-45 blue 56-78 orange 1-100 green 120-156 red A file of ranges to colour (one range per line) can be specified as '@filename'.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="float" name="plurality" qname="appInputs>plurality"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>Set a cut-off for the % of positive scoring matches below which there is no consensus. The default plurality is taken as 50% of the total weight of all the sequences in the alignment.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="float" name="setcase" qname="appInputs>setcase"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>Sets the threshold for the scores of the positive matches above which the consensus is in upper-case and below which the consensus is in lower-case. By default this is set to be half of the (weight-adjusted) number of sequences in the alignment.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="float" name="identity" qname="appInputs>identity"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>Provides the facility of setting the required number of identities at a position for it to give a consensus. Therefore, if this is set to 100% only columns of identities contribute to the consensus.</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype><s:basetype optional="true" unbounded="false" typename="boolean" name="gaps" qname="appInputs>gaps"><xsd:annotation xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><xsd:documentation>If this option is true then gap characters can appear in the consensus. The alternative is 'N' for nucleotide, or 'X' for protein</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation></s:basetype></s:elements></s:complextype></s:extensions>
